com.azure.storage.blob

Class ContainerSASPermission

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.azure.storage.blob.ContainerSASPermission

  • public final class ContainerSASPermission
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a helper class to construct a string representing the permissions granted by a ServiceSAS to a container. Setting a value to true means that any SAS which uses these permissions will grant permissions for that operation. Once all the values are set, this should be serialized with toString and set as the permissions field on a ServiceSASSignatureValues object. It is possible to construct the permissions string without this class, but the order of the permissions is particular and this class guarantees correctness.

      • parse

        public static ContainerSASPermission parse(java.lang.String permString)
        Creates an ContainerSASPermission from the specified permissions string. This method will throw an IllegalArgumentException if it encounters a character that does not correspond to a valid permission.
        Parameters:
        permString - A String which represents the ContainerSASPermission.
        Returns:
        A ContainerSASPermission generated from the given String.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If permString contains a character other than r, a, c, w, d, or l.
